videos.description: With the clock winding down in the first half, Kansas' Frank Mason III draws in the entire Kansas State defense before kicking it out to Brannen Greene, who hits the three and gets fouled. The Jayhawks would finish the 4-point play.
videos.headline: Clock running down? Might as well end the half with a 4-point play

videos.description: Kansas coach Bill Self sends out best wishes to Holly Rowe and points out how he's got to deal with Fran Fraschilla instead at halftime.
videos.headline: Bill Self tells Holly Rowe to get back soon

videos.headline: Kansas picks up another victory in the Big 12

videos.description: With Kansas already up by 16 over Kansas State, Jayhawks G Brannen Greene throws down a dunk in the game's final seconds to extend the lead to 18, later prompting coach Bill Self to condemn the play.
